  "prompt": "Can I download and listen to music in offline mode on the Spotify app on Volvo Sensus?",
  "response": "Volvo Sensus is an infotainment system found in Volvo vehicles, and it offers various features including navigation, entertainment, and connectivity. As of my last update in October 2023, Spotify compatibility can vary depending on the specific version of the Volvo Sensus system and any updates that may have been released.\n\nTypically, the Spotify app on Volvo Sensus allows you to stream music directly to your car through an internet connection. For offline listening, you generally need to have a Spotify Premium subscription, and the process usually involves downloading the songs on your mobile device first. Once downloaded, you can then play the music offline through a connected device (such as your smartphone) via Bluetooth or USB.\n\nHowever, the capability to download and store music directly onto the Sensus system for offline listening is not a standard feature. You should check with Volvo customer service or your vehicle\u2019s manual for the most current information around this feature, as updates and enhancements can change the functionality over time.",
